File: Minister Lindiwe Sisulu has appointed Terry Motau to lead lawyers in reviewing all fraud, corruption and irregular expenditure reports in her department. JOHANNESBURG - The Human Settlements, Water and Sanitation Minister is determined to make her staff suffer the consequences of dodgy actions. Lindiwe Sisulu has appointed Terry Motau to lead lawyers in reviewing all fraud, corruption and irregular expenditure reports in her department. Part of Motau's job is to ensure the implementation of all recommendations made. READ: Water and Sanitisation Department officials probed for corruption The investigations will include Water Boards and senior managers of the Water and Sanitation Department. According to Sisulu, projects worth more than R16-billion have been issued irregularly. Motau is the advocate who investigated corruption and looting at VBS Bank in Limpopo.